      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Camaro fans are going to get worked up over this, especially since there have been rumors about the muscle car’s demise for a while without any official announcement. So technically the Camaro didn’t die this year and its end wasn’t announced. Instead, something possibly even worse happened.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Not only does the Camaro keep coming in dead last for its market segment by a big margin, GM decided to shelve production for a big chunk of 2021. It was like a soft or trial cancellation, plus it indicates the automaker doesn’t have much faith in people wanting the Camaro. That’s a bitter pill to swallow.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
